div.row-fluid
  div.span12
    div.hero-unit(style='padding:15px;margin-bottom:20px;text-align:center')
      h2 Asterank is an economic and scientific catalog of over 580,000 asteroids in our solar system.

    div.welcome-blurb.well
      img(style='float:right;padding-left:15px;padding-bottom:11px;width:auto;height:200px', src='http://i.imgur.com/vvAjG.jpg')
      h2 Overview
      p.spacey Asteroid mining has been <a href="http://www.space.com/15395-asteroid-mining-planetary-resources.html" target="_blank">in the news</a> recently. Companies like Planetary Resources are an exciting take on the commercial viability of space industry.  But how realistic are the trillion dollar estimates?  How much would it cost to mine an object millions of miles away?

      p.spacey(style='font-weight: bold;') We've collected, computed, or inferred important data points such as asteroid mass and composition using scraped data from multiple scientific sources.  With this information, we estimate the costs and rewards of mining rocks in space.

      h2 Data
      p Details on orbits and basic physical parameters are mostly sourced from JPL data.  Composition data is harder to come by.  We make generalizations about asteroids based on their spectral classification and size.  Although scientists know very little about the actual composition of different classes of asteroids, our calculations incorporate conclusions from multiple scientific publications in addition to cross-referencing known meteorite data.

      //
        p There are three major factors:
          ol
            li <strong>Value of Materials</strong> - Many asteroids contain metals, volatile compounds, and water.
            li <strong>Cost of Operations</strong> - Getting to an asteroid and moving the raw material isn't easy or cheap (yet).
            li <strong>Comparative Savings</strong> - The biggest obstacle to the commercialization of space is getting things into orbit.  How much money do we save by mining in space instead of sending material from Earth?

      p.spacey The data on these objects are public but very sparse.  It's 2012 and there are no "experts" in this field.  Assumptions are made.

    div.well(style='text-align:center;')
      noscript
        div(style='margin-bottom:30px;')
          h3 Sorry, JavaScript is required to perform searches!  I track usage to determine data that I should prioritize when scraping and features that need improvement.  For a version of the homepage with no 3rd-party social content (eg. Facebook, Twitter share), click <a href="/?nosocial">here</a>.

      form.form-inline(style='margin:0')
        div.search-thing
          span Show top
          select#top_num(style='margin:0 5px 0').input-small
            option(value=100) 100
            option(value=1000) 1,000
            option(value=5000) 5,000
            option(value=10000) 10,000+
          span  asteroids sorted by
          select#top_sort(style='margin:0 5px 0').input-xlarge
            option(value='profit') profit
            option(value='score', selected) most cost effective
            option(value='price') most valuable
            option(value='closeness') accessibility
          input#submit.btn.btn-large.btn-primary(type='submit', value='Go', style='width:175px;margin-left:15px')

